{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5451d09b-0f4b-472f-a98c-d721fbcacea3","content":"With **MSTest 3.8.2**, the modern approach is:\n\n- **`TestContext`** — inject via **constructor** (no more static property).\n- **Sync init** — use the constructor or `[TestInitialize]`.\n- **Async init** — use `[TestInitialize]` returning `async Task`.\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private HttpClient _client = null!;\n\n    // Constructor: sync init + TestContext injection\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // Async init\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        _client = new HttpClient();\n        await _client.GetAsync(\"https://example.com/health\");\n    }\n\n    [TestCleanup]\n    public void Cleanup() => _client?.Dispose();\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void ExampleTest()\n    {\n        _testContext.WriteLine(\"Running test...\");\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_client);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- Constructor injection of `TestContext` replaced the legacy `public static TestContext TestContext { get; set; }` pattern.\n- `[TestInitialize]` supports `async Task` for async setup.\n- Use `[TestCleanup]` (sync or async) for teardown.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ff38e312-6f04-4151-b54e-5a7684c34e02","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"They're using MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9.0. In MSTest v3, the recommended modern approach is:\n\n1. **TestContext injection**: Use constructor injection (`TestContext` as a constructor parameter) instead of the legacy static property pattern.\n2. **Synchronous init**: Use the constructor or `[TestInitialize]` method.\n3. **Asynchronous init**: Use `[TestInitialize]` with `async Task` return type (supported in MSTest v3).\n\nIn MSTest 3.x, `TestContext` can be injected via constructor. The old pattern was a static `TestContext` property with a setter, but the modern way is constructor injection.\n\n\nNow I'll provide a straightforward answer about how to set this up.","outputTokens":529,"requestId":"702D:215959:BA8697:D89919:69F2B04F"},"id":"3fb38565-0ece-4cd3-ab50-0db56603cc36","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:28:58.228Z","parentId":"47f80cba-0c0d-49c1-a630-213ba09b0137"}
